      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e\u003e Now that DefaultTarget is called A LOT more often, it would be better to get rid of defaultTargetLock and .Clone() and instead use atomic.Value and clone in \u0027SetDefaultTarget\u0027\nActually, defaultTargetLock is sync.RWMutex, and DefaultTarget() only acquires the read lock.\n\nhttps://golang.org/pkg/sync/#RWMutex\n\u003e\u003e The lock can be held by an arbitrary number of readers or a single writer.\n\nAll the concurrent goroutines, invoking DefaultTarget(), will be blocked by the read-lock, only during the execution of SetDefaultTarget(). However, I don\u0027t think that applications invoke SetDefaultTarget() in parallel to running a number of goroutines, each may invoke metric.Set()/Get()/Incr().\n\nIf an application needs to iterate through all of the existing business objects and report a metric data for each of the business object, then the target context should be used instead of SetDefaultTarget().\n\ne.g.,\n```\nfor _, bot :\u003d model.SwarmingBots {\n  tctx :\u003d target.Set(ctx, ToNetworkDevice(bot))\n  bot_status_metric.Set(tctx, bot.Status)\n}\n```\n\nIndeed, in the existing semantics, SetDefaultTarget() cannot be used instead of target.Set() in the above example. Whichever target object passed onto the last invocation of s.SetDefaultTarget() will be used for all the metrics.\n\nIdeally, I\u0027d love to remove SetDefaultTarget(), and DefaultTarget returns an immutable target object that can be set only via the construct of Store objects.\n: e.g., store :\u003d NewInMemory(defaultTarget)\n\nThe only use case that I can think of use SetDefaultTarget() is to change the tasknum of the default target object for acquisitions.Task target. The tasknum assigner will be my first target to deprecate and kill, if I could with migrating all the existing metrics from acqusitions.Task to something like, chops.Http or prpc.Task.\n\n----------------------------------------------------------\n\nIf it\u0027s a still concern that DefaultTarget() acquires the read-lock, then please let me know. I will make the change, as you proposed.",
      "parentUuid": "b401005d_b4ebfe74",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 174,
        "startChar": 24,
